"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn scatterplot function already includes a legend by default if the hue parameter is used. However, in this case, the hue parameter is not used, so there is no need to call ax.legend(). If you want to include a legend, you should specify the hue parameter.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7,8c7,8\\n< sbn.scatterplot(data=tips, x='total_bill', y='tip', ax=ax)\\n< ax.legend()\\n---\\n> sbn.scatterplot(data=tips, x='total_bill', y='tip', hue='sex', ax=ax)\\n> # ax.legend()  # This line can be removed or commented out\"\n}"